  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 3, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Sleeptab collects nothing. Your sleep data is read on your device and never leaves it.</p>

  <h2>Health data</h2>
  <p>With your permission, Sleeptab reads sleep records from Apple Health to calculate your sleep
     debt. All processing happens on your device. Your health data is never uploaded, shared, or
     used for anything other than showing you your own numbers. You can revoke access at any time
     in Settings → Health → Data Access &amp; Devices.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Summaries Sleeptab computes (like your nightly totals) are stored locally on your device so
     the app and its widget can display them. Your data never touches our servers, because we
     don't have any.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No accounts. No analytics. No ads. No third-party SDKs. No tracking of any kind. We never
     use Health data for marketing, and we never disclose it to third parties.</p>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>The one-time unlock is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We never see your
     payment details.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/sleeptab/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
